OL,7,FNot necessarily vibrant, energetic
OL,8,Flife. But a calm, contemplative
OL,9,Fatmosphere, where life can be savoured
OL,10,Fand reflected upon.
OL,12,FReflection is indeed a big part of the
OL,13,Fwork of a hospice ` helping people to
OL,14,Fcome to terms with their terminal
OL,15,Fillness, or the grief their family is
OL,16,Fabout to experience.
OL,18,FNow, they are reflecting on a new
OL,19,Fdynamic. Whether life should be
OL,20,Fshortened via assisted dying.
