OL,4,Cbut they are divided over assisted
OL,5,Cdying
OL,7,FThe debate sparked by Kim Leadbeater
OL,8,FMP's private members' bill has huge
OL,9,Fconsequences for the hospice sector.
OL,11,FIn other countries where assisted
OL,12,Fdying has been legalised already,
OL,13,Fhospices have gone from prolonging
OL,14,Flife and easing suffering, to in some
OL,15,Fcases shortening life and ending pain
OL,16,Faltogether.
OL,18,FAnd yet despite the huge implications,
OL,19,Fthe UK hospice sector is taking a
OL,20,Fneutral stance on the matter.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
