OL,4,Cbut they are divided over assisted
OL,5,Cdying
OL,7,FAt Royal Trinity, you can understand
OL,8,Fwhy.
OL,10,FI've come to hear how staff and
OL,11,Fpatients here feel about assisted
OL,12,Fdying and it is immediately clear that
OL,13,Fthey are deeply ` though very
OL,14,Frespectfully ` divided over the matter.
OL,16,FOne of the first people I meet is 77-
OL,17,Fyear-old Terry Davie. He arrived at
OL,18,Fthe hospice two nights ago and has
OL,19,Fterminal cancer. He knows he will not
OL,20,Fleave.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
