OL,7,FIt is a difficult conversation to have
OL,8,Fwith him, but Terry tells me he would
OL,9,Flike more control over how long he's
OL,10,Flikely to stay for.
OL,12,F"I don't want to be suffering in a
OL,13,Fsituation where the obvious is known,"
OL,14,Fhe says.
OL,16,F"If there's an opportunity to nip it
OL,17,Fin the bud, then I'd do it."
OL,19,F"You would like the option of an
OL,20,Fassisted death?" I ask.
