OL,4,Cbut they are divided over assisted
OL,5,Cdying
OL,7,FTerry and Mary Anne are being looked
OL,8,Fafter by a team of doctors and nurses,
OL,9,Fas well as counsellors and spiritual
OL,10,Fmentors who guide them through their
OL,11,Fanxieties and grief.
OL,13,FThese staff are experts in death, yet
OL,14,Fthey each have a different view on how
OL,15,Fbest to manage the end of life.
OL,17,F"We want to think that everyone is
OL,18,Fgoing to go peacefully in their sleep
OL,19,Fand thankfully many people do," senior
OL,20,Fcounsellor Claire Moor tells me.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
