OL,7,FBut she feels that even a brilliant
OL,8,Fhospice can't always provide a good
OL,9,Fdeath.
OL,11,F"If you've got a terminal illness and
OL,12,Fyour body is being taken over by your
OL,13,Fdisease, there's no guarantee of that.
OL,15,F"And for some people the thought of
OL,16,Fgoing towards that is understandably
OL,17,Fvery frightening for them. And they
OL,18,Falso don't want their loved ones to
OL,19,Fwitness it.
