OL,7,F"So they want the choice to die with
OL,8,Fdignity. And dignity is the key word
OL,9,Fwhen thinking about assisted dying."
OL,11,FClaire tells me that assisted dying
OL,12,Fhas come up many times in the
OL,13,Fconversations she's had with patients,
OL,14,Fperhaps because they feel her
OL,15,Fcounselling sessions are a safe
OL,16,Fenvironment in which to raise it.
OL,18,FShe cannot help to explore the option
OL,19,Fof course, because under the current
OL,20,Flaw to do so might be illegal.
